{title: The Shrine Of Saint Cecilia}
{artist: Faron Young}
{composer: unknown}

[Fm]A storm came from up above
But some[C]how it missed
The [F]Shrine of [G7]Saint [C]Cecilia
The bells in the chapel
[F]Never ring any[G7]more
The [C]clock in the steeple
Can't [F]tell time as before
[Fm]But up on the hillside
Stands a [C]place heaven blessed
The [F]Shrine of [G7]Saint [C]Cecilia
[F]Each day at even [C]tide
When I [F]seek haven from my [G7]daily [C]care
You'll [D7]find me by her side
It seems so peaceful [G7]there
[C]I kneel in my solitude [F]and silently [G7]pray
That [C]heaven will protect you dear
And [F]there'll come a day
